<title>USA: Talbots doesn't see Q2 making up for Q1.</title>
<headline>Talbots doesn't see Q2 making up for Q1.</headline>
<dateline>HINGHAM, Mass. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Talbots Inc said Thursday that it does not expect its second quarter earnings to make up for the catalogue sales shortfall that occurred in the first quarter.</p>
<p>However, the clothing retailer said it anticipates earnings-per-share growth in the second quarter, driven by catalogue adjustments that are being made and increased sales during its semiannual sale in June and July.</p>
<p>In the prior year's second quarter, Talbots posted net income of $6.61 million, or $0.20 per share.</p>
